                  "title": "The First Night",
                  "author": "Elder Dreamer",
                  "pages": [
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "On the first true night, the Dreamers discovered that sleep was not rest \u2014 it was return. In sleep, they touched the source of all things.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "The first Dreamer to sleep was terrified. They thought they were dying. Instead, they found themselves in a place with no ground and no sky, where thoughts were visible and feelings had weight.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "They woke and tried to describe it. The only word they found was: home.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "\n\n  ",
